title: Introduction to programming
description: Programming is the act of instructing computers to carry out tasks

title: Intermediate programming
description: Intermediate Programming. To change directions for a second, I'd like to define the term intermediate programming. I feel like intermediate programming is the level of programming most non-senior professional programmers occupy.

title: advanced programming
description: Advanced Programming Concepts. Advanced Programming Concepts. Advanced software development with an object-oriented focus. Design, implementation, and testing of several large programs in a Java and Linux environment using current technologies.

title: Internet of things
description: The Internet of Things is a system of interrelated computing devices, mechanical and digital machines, objects, animals or people that are provided with unique identifiers and the ability to transfer data over a network without requiring human-to-human or human-to-computer interaction.

title: Object-oriented programming
description: Object-oriented programming is a programming paradigm based on the concept of "objects", which can contain data, in the form of fields, and code, in the form of procedures.

title: Introduction to AI
description: In computer science, artificial intelligence, sometimes called machine intelligence, is intelligence demonstrated by machines, in contrast to the natural intelligence displayed by humans.

title: Business Analytics
description: Business analytics refers to the skills, technologies, practices for continuous iterative exploration and investigation of past business performance to gain insight and drive business planning.

title: Financial technology
description: Financial technology, often shortened to fintech, is the technology and innovation that aims to compete with traditional financial methods in the delivery of financial services. It is an emerging industry that uses technology to improve activities in finance.

title: Business Process Improvement
description: Business process improvement (BPI) is a management exercise in which enterprise leaders use various methodologies to analyze their procedures to identify areas where they can improve accuracy, effectiveness and/or efficiency and then redesign those processes to realize the improvements.

title: Introduction for Business Studies
description: Business studies is the study of the management of individuals to maintain collective productivity, which accomplishes particular creative and productive goals, usually to generate profits.

title: Business Studies
description: combines elements of accountancy, finance, marketing, organizational studies and economics. Business Studies is a broad subject in the Social Sciences, allowing the in-depth study of a range of specialties such as accountancy, finance, organisation, human resources management and marketing

title: Introduction to economics
description: Economics is the social science of studying the production, distribution and consumption of goods and services and It is a complex social science that spans from mathematics to psychology

title: Microeconomics
description: Microeconomics is a branch of economics that studies the behaviour of individuals and firms in making decisions regarding the allocation of scarce resources and the interactions among these individuals and firms.

title: Macroeconomics
description: Macroeconomics is a branch of economics dealing with the performance, structure, behavior, and decision-making of an economy as a whole. This includes regional, national, and global economies.
